    "body": "that's a solution I've used before, but the issue is that it takes a long\ntime if the matrices are large (thousands of columns), and I'm not\ninterested in the df1,df2 correlations, necessarily.\n\nOn Mon, Apr 6, 2015 at 4:58 PM jreback notifications@github.com wrote:\n\n> In [58]: pd.concat([df1,df2],axis=1).corr()\n> Out[58]:\n>           A         B         C         D         E         0         1         2         3         4\n> A  1.000000  0.160876  0.368649  0.252098  0.108760  0.566828 -0.466817 -0.314223 -0.131133  0.590715\n> B  0.160876  1.000000  0.545311  0.056020 -0.460356 -0.091174  0.354608 -0.378924 -0.003633 -0.048977\n> C  0.368649  0.545311  1.000000 -0.451701 -0.165686 -0.036762  0.253964  0.036151  0.125651  0.145658\n> D  0.252098  0.056020 -0.451701  1.000000 -0.257068  0.735342 -0.185773 -0.589945  0.138441  0.006919\n> E  0.108760 -0.460356 -0.165686 -0.257068  1.000000  0.035644 -0.570018 -0.012733 -0.293044  0.464915\n> 0  0.566828 -0.091174 -0.036762  0.735342  0.035644  1.000000 -0.188574 -0.525456  0.359605  0.347547\n> 1 -0.466817  0.354608  0.253964 -0.185773 -0.570018 -0.188574  1.000000 -0.056621  0.627198 -0.289038\n> 2 -0.314223 -0.378924  0.036151 -0.589945 -0.012733 -0.525456 -0.056621  1.000000  0.041765 -0.069550\n> 3 -0.131133 -0.003633  0.125651  0.138441 -0.293044  0.359605  0.627198  0.041765  1.000000  0.287847\n> 4  0.590715 -0.048977  0.145658  0.006919  0.464915  0.347547 -0.289038 -0.069550  0.287847  1.000000\n> \n> â€”\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/pydata/pandas/issues/9823#issuecomment-90291610.\n"
